### `handle_input` function

Handles user input (arrow keys) to update the snake's direction.
```c
void handle_input(SDL_Event event) {
    if (event.type == SDL_KEYDOWN) {
        switch (event.key.keysym.sym) {
            case SDLK_UP:
                snake.direction.x = 0; snake.direction.y = -1;
                break;
            case SDLK_DOWN:
                snake.direction.x = 0; snake.direction.y = 1;
                break;
            case SDLK_LEFT:
                snake.direction.x = -1; snake.direction.y = 0;
                break;
            case SDLK_RIGHT:
                snake.direction.x = 1; snake.direction.y = 0;
                break;
        }
    }
}
```
### `check_collisions` function

Checks for collisions between the snake, food, and boundaries.
```c
void check_collisions(struct Snake* snake, struct Food* food) {
    // Snake-self collision detection
    for (int i = 1; i < snake->length; i++) {
