class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false; // 0 and negative numbers are not powers of three
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution works by calculating the logarithm of `n` with base 3. If `n` is a power of three, the result will be an integer (i.e., the exponent `x`). The `% 1 == 0` check verifies if the result is an integer, returning `true` if it is, and `false` otherwise. The time complexity is constant because logarithm calculations are optimized in most programming languages and don't involve loops or recursion.

